				<td colspan="2"><span>Ive expressed this before so pardon my repetition - what you are feeling is natural for a low level bard - which is why I quit playing Tin at about 16 only to realize later (much later) what a force they are.  The reason you feel like you are not contributing is that with all other classes there is immediate feedback wrt your contribution.  For bards that is not always the case.  Singing haste and resists and below doesnt give us a very good feeling for what we have added - you basically feel like a crappy tank.  However, what others will often notice is that things go much smoother and your group is able to accomplish more.  You just need the confidence that you are doing your part and it is just as valuable as the other members of your group.  Trust me (and the rest of us) it is.
<br />

