				<td colspan="2"><span>Without going into specific songs and situations, as they've been covered nicely in posts above me: In a good group, the bard ideally is the grease that keeps everything running smoothly. You won't get the killshots or the high crits, but you'll notice that everyone starts commenting on how incredibly well the group's doing. This is quite likely to be your fault.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
In a bad group, the bard can be the one thing that stands between the group and a total wipeout. I had an LDoN group so bad it should be illegal just a few days ago.. Cleric ran out of mana every 4 mobs with C3 AND level 55 manasong, SK insisted on offtanking adds I already mezzed (despite the aforementioned cleric's manapool) and our main tank got lost roughly 4 times in a 60 minute adventure. The only reason we got through and did so well within the timelimit was because I steadily fed them singlepulls. The three or four pulls that had adds were mezzed, when the SK broke it I would try and snatch up and mob with loose aggro, there always was a manasong going so the cleric could do at least a few pulls without needing a break, hastes were always up (I think we might've had a shammy.. not sure, there never was any spellhaste anyways).. I basically spoonfed these people their XP in small, easily swallowed packages. 
<br />

<br />
Tell me any other class who can make a group like that look good. (To the extent that these people were clamoring for another one, because &quot;this one went so well!&quot;.. Ugh. Quickly disbanded.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />)</span></td>
