				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what are bards really for..<a name="26903"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 04 7:21 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><b>Chanter class</b>.
<br />

<br />
Pull: Pacify.
<br />
DPS: Charmed pet.
<br />

<br />
A bit longer pulls since charmed pet can break (so no pulling at 50% HPs), shorter kills, tanks get less DMG, less heals, less med, SOV haste, 70% slow.
<br />

<br />
<b>Necro class</b> in Guk LDoNs.
<br />

<br />
Pull: Pet pulls (only with regular pet, not with charmed pet)
<br />
DPS: Dots and Rogue pet or charmed eye.
<br />
Heals: A h*ll of a lot better heals than bard class. Less downtime on healer with crappy mana pool.
<br />
Mana: Necro Twich on healer. Less med needed.
<br />

<br />
Only backdraw is no haste on melee. Necro 70% slow, necro mez if needed. Pet pull should get no adds, also FD option.</span></td>
