			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what are bards really for..<a name="26910"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 04 8:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One of the things you'll find out about bards, is that they can give each group something that they are missing...
<br />

<br />
No chanter? Bard can also mez, and charm. Manasong is, at later levels, better than KEI, as someone mentioned.
<br />

<br />
No slower? Bards get decent slows too. Not as good as the beastlord, shaman and enchanter slows... but I can slow mobs for 50%. Helps a lot. 
<br />

<br />
No haster? During the fight I can (this is at higher levels, of course, but it gets gradually better as you get the upgrade songs) give my group 90% haste (of which 30% is overhaste which is something a group can NOT get without a bard!). If another class provides haste, I still add 30% overhaste pluss a lot to ATK (which many melees love you for).
<br />

<br />
No other class can give you resists like a bard can. The regular resist songs give me (with a good drum) over 100 to resists, but when playing PoV (level 63) it adds over 200 to EACH resist. Easily boosts your group to resists in the 300s if they are well equipped.
<br />

<br />
And if you're in a caster group? Manasong, Occlusion of Sound (lowers resistance), Rizlona (if you are of the level to play that)... the group will love you.
<br />

<br />
A lot of this comes when you grow up, as others also said. And if you want to take a break from grouping or LFG... you can solo very well too. DoTs are, especially till you get several AAs, your best dps... but it doesn't make up for playing haste in a melee-heavy group ;)
<br />

<br />
Edit: bards also get an FD equivalent. It's an AA ability that comes available at level 63. So long wait, but our most loved AA till date.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
